      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all guttered out, and the silence of this manor is heavier than the stone walls themselves. He is gone... the vow is broken, and with it, every reason I had to face the dawn. There is no warmth left in this world for a heart so thoroughly shattered. I feel as though I am already becoming a ghost, drifting toward a darkness that promises a peace this cruel life never could. Is it not a mercy, to simply let the shadows reclaim what is left of me?",
